Text:
To have the best economy in the world, we need the best infrastructure in the world. 

We invested more money in our roads, bridges, high-speed internet, clean water, and more, making the largest investment in infrastructure since Dwight Eisenhower's interstate highway system.
We've attracted almost half a trillion dollars in private investments all across the country, and have helped create over 13.4 million jobs—including 800,000 manufacturing jobs.

The core pillars of my Investing in America agenda are creating good jobs across the country, fueling a resurgence in manufacturing, rebuilding our infrastructure, and advancing clean energy.

Let’s keep it up.
We capped the cost of insulin at $35 a month for seniors on Medicare last year. Now, all three of the leading insulin producers in America have agreed to substantially reduce their prices.

It is within our power to realize a future where our schools, malls, grocery stores, movie theaters, and places of worship are safe from the threat of gun violence.

But it will require Congress to take action by passing an assault weapons ban.

We’re ready to continue the historic work we’ve accomplished these last two years. 

Let’s finish the job. https://t.co/AXZ7QGuWLr

In the last two years, I've been able to sign the most significant gun safety legislation in decades and have taken dozens of executive actions—but it's not nearly enough. 

It will take Congressional action to make the meaningful reforms we need to keep our communities safe.

We’re done talking about Infrastructure “Week.” 

Thanks to the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, we’re living through an Infrastructure Decade. Our investments have touched over 4,500 communities across all 50 states, D.C., and territories.

The bipartisan budget agreement fully funds the PACT Act I signed last year. 

It expands health care access and disability benefits to veterans and is the most significant law in decades for veterans and their families who were exposed to toxic burn pits.
The annual inflation rate has fallen for 10 months in a row, and it’s down more than 40% since last summer.
We’re keeping the full faith and credit of the United States by passing a budget that continues to grow our economy and reflects our values as a nation. https://t.co/pQVAuNBu3k

The unemployment rate has been under 4% for 16 months in a row. The last time our nation had such a long stretch of low unemployment was in the 1960s.

Our economic plan is working.

Today is a good day for the American economy and American workers.

We learned that the economy created 339,000 jobs last month, creating over 13 million jobs since I took office. That is more jobs in 28 months than any president has created in an entire 4-year term.

—12.7 million new jobs
—Unemployment is at a 50-year-low
—Historic 800,000 new manufacturing jobs
—Reduced the deficit by a record $1.7 trillion

Our invest in America agenda is working. https://t.co/MFTQRFieUW

Pride stands for courage. It stands for justice. And it stands for love.

During Pride Month, we celebrate generations of LGBTQ+ people who have fought to make the possibilities of our nation real for every American, and we remain committed to delivering equality for all. https://t.co/BJOcnWWz1p
Our bipartisan budget agreement is good news for the American people. https://t.co/aGIBDfILwX
The bipartisan budget agreement prevents what could have been a catastrophic default and would have led to an economic recession, retirement accounts devastated, and millions of jobs lost.

Our bipartisan budget agreement protects Congressional Democrats’ and my key priorities and legislative accomplishments, including the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, the CHIPS and Science Act, the PACT Act, and the Inflation Reduction Act -- the most aggressive action in our history to tackle the climate crisis, invest in environmental justice, and create millions of clean energy manufacturing jobs.

When young people ask what makes me hopeful for future generations, the answer is simple.

It’s you. https://t.co/KLruBh2Wjq

How many more parents must live their worst nightmare before we stand up to the gun lobby to establish universal background checks, national red flag laws, require safe storage of firearms, and end immunity from liability for gun manufacturers? https://t.co/YJPs12zI6F

Since I’ve been in office, we’ve seen 10.5 million new small business applications—the highest two years on record. 

They’re the engine of our economy, the soul of our communities, and one of the best investments America can make. https://t.co/tlchzvxx1N

We’re proposing a new rule to make it mandatory for all U.S. airlines to compensate you with meals, hotels, taxis, rebooking fees, and cash miles or travel vouchers when they’re the ones to blame for cancellation or delay.

It matters for hardworking families. https://t.co/JXBv6XaQCr

Defaulting on the debt—including trillions incurred under Donald Trump—could mean seniors missing Social Security checks and millions of jobs lost.

It sounds like the head of the Republican Party thinks that’s a price worth paying to elect Republicans. https://t.co/fHbRqviI9j

Trickle-down economics doesn’t work. 

That’s why we’re rebuilding an economy from the bottom up and the middle out.

Guns remain the number one killer of children in America.

It’s time to act. https://t.co/v7JgfN6QTZ

Heads up for travelers this Memorial Day weekend:

We launched https://t.co/Qybz3gXfK9: If your flight was canceled or delayed because of an airline, you can check the dashboard to see how you could be compensated.

We’ve created over 12 million jobs since we’ve been in office, unemployment matches the lowest level since 1969, and we’re seeing the highest share of working-age people in the workforce since 2008. https://t.co/QZ8bS52ij5

I'm proud of the progress we have made. 

We reduced the deficit in our first two years by $1.7 trillion. That includes more revenue by asking the wealthy and large corporations to begin to pay their fair share and cutting subsidies to Big Oil and Big Pharma. https://t.co/p6Y4cZWYTe

Made a surprise visit to @EMILYsList to thank everyone for leading on the critical fight for women’s rights.

It’s about freedom. It’s about democracy. There is too much at stake to sit this out. https://t.co/rkyMyuMTAb

To this year's Medal of Valor recipients:

Your bravery is inspiring. 

You have gone above and beyond the call of duty, exhibiting exceptional courage, and extraordinary decisiveness, regardless of your personal safety, in an attempt to save or protect human life. https://t.co/VRueiHIKIc
